[2]
Date: Sat 4 Feb 2017
Source: Espacio de Prensa, Agencia EFE report [in Spanish, trans. KS, edited Mods.JT/JG]
https://www.espaciodeprensa.com/registran-brasil-64-casos-una-extrana-mialgia-deja-la-orina-negra/


Health officials have reported in the state of Bahia, northeast Brazil, 64 cases of a strange myalgia that causes intense muscle pain and black urine, officials said today [7 Feb 2017].

The state medical services are investigating the still unknown causes of the outbreak of this type of acute myalgia, whose 1st case was notified on 14 Dec 12016, according to a statement from the Bahia Health Ministry.

Of the total number of patients reported with this strange condition, 60 are from Salvador, capital of Bahia, and 33 fit the definition of sudden acute myalgia, so that practically half of the patients have no clear diagnosis.

The symptoms are intense muscle pains, which affect "mainly the cervical and trapezius region" and the upper and lower limbs, in addition to the black urine, the report added.

The Government of Bahia, with the support of the Brazilian Ministry of Health, announced an international cooperation agreement with the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC), in the United States, to intensify the search for the cause(s) of this outbreak.

"It will be necessary to review the files and analyze the data bank built in these 2 months and, if necessary, interview the patients and health professionals who attended them," said State Health Undersecretary Roberto Badaro, quoted in the note.

Some of the samples are being analyzed by the Brazilian Oswaldo Cruz Foundation, the largest center for health studies in Latin America.

